cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on comparing the performance of different web protocol stacks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of TLS in the protocol stacks being compared. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper discusses the impact of network conditions on performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses the tuning of TCP parameters for improved performance. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possibility as the paper focuses on comparing the performance of different protocol stacks.
